This paper discusses the design philosophy for interoperable blockchain systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also discusses the challenges of cross-domain transactions, which could be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the design principles of the Internet architecture, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.DL) as well.
